  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I'm a US citizen and my boyfriend is Argentinean; if we get married in the US, how long will it take for him to be qualified to work in the US?",
  "response": "If you get married in the US, your Argentinean husband can pursue a path to legal residency, which will allow him to work in the United States. Here's a general outline of the process:\n\n1. **Marriage and Petitioning**: After your marriage, you, as a US citizen, can file Form I-130 (Petition for Alien Relative) to establish the relationship. Simultaneously, your husband can file Form I-485 (Application to Register Permanent Residence or Adjust Status) if he is already in the US. This is known as concurrent filing.\n\n2. **Work Authorization**: Your husband can also file Form I-765 (Application for Employment Authorization) along with the I-485. This form is for requesting an Employment Authorization Document (EAD), which will allow him to work legally in the US.\n\n3. **Processing Time**: \n   - The typical processing time for a work permit (EAD) based on marriage can range from a few months to about six months or more, although this can vary based on the workload of the specific USCIS service center handling the case.\n   - The entire adjustment of status process to obtain a Green Card can take longer, often between 8 to 14 months or more, depending on the specifics of the case and the processing times at USCIS.\n\n4. **Biometrics Appointment and Interview**: As part of the process, your husband will likely be required to attend a biometrics appointment and an interview at a USCIS office.\n\n5. **Approval and Green Card**: Once his application is approved, he will receive a Green Card (permanent residency), which allows him to live and work in the US permanently.\n\nAll times are approximate and can be affected by changes in policy, caseload, and other factors. It's important to ensure all forms are accurately filled out and required documents are submitted, as errors can delay processing. Consulting with an immigration attorney can provide personalized guidance and help navigate the process more smoothly.",
